IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: JUNIOR ACHIEVEMENT OF WISCONSIN, INC. SERVES A FRANCHISED AREA OF JUNIOR ACHIEVEMENT WORLDWIDE, INC. THE ORGANIZATION WAS CREATED FOR THE PURPOSE OF ENHANCING WISCONSIN'S ECONOMIC VITALITY BY PROVIDING YOUNG PEOPLE AND THE CHANGING WORKFORCE WITH EXPERIENCE-BASED ECONOMIC EDUCATION THROUGH PARTNERSHIPS THAT ARE RESPONSIVE TO BUSINESS, EDUCATION, AND COMMUNITY NEEDS. THE ORGANIZATION EDUCATES AND INSPIRES YOUNG PEOPLE TO VALUE FREE ENTERPRISE, UNDERSTAND BUSINESS AND ECONOMICS AND BECOME BETTER PREPARED FOR THE WORKFORCE THROUGH A VARIETY OF PROGRAMS SPECIFICALLY DEVELOPED FOR VARIOUS AGE GROUPS.

IRS990.Description: HIGH SCHOOL PROGRAMS-ECONOMIC & BUSINESS CURRICULA (INCLUDING A STUDENT-LED ENTERPRISE) FOR 22,585 STUDENTS IN 1,044 CLASSROOMS IN GRADES 9-12.

Activity2.Description: MIDDLE GRADE PROGRAMS-ECONOMICS & BUSINESS CURRICULA FOR 29,229 7TH, 8TH & 9TH GRADE STUDENTS IN 1,332 CLASSROOMS. THE DYNAMIC INTERACTION BETWEEN VOLUNTEERS & STUDENTS PROMOTES ACTIVE LEARNING AND BRINGS THEORY TO LIFE.

Activity3.Description: ELEMENTARY SCHOOL PROGRAMS-THE FOUNDATION OF THE K-12 CURRICULA FOR 113,952 STUDENTS IN 5,531 CLASSROOMS. SEVEN SEQUENTIAL THEMES, EACH WITH FIVE HANDS-ON ACTIVITIES, WORK TO CHANGE KIDS' LIVES BY HELPING THEM UNDERSTAND BUSINESS & ECONOMICS.

ActivityOther.Description: CAPSTONE PROGRAMS - JA BIZTOWN AND JA FINANCE PARK - THROUGH THESE TWO PROGRAMS, STUDENTS WILL LEARN IN A 36,000 SQUARE FOOT FACILITY WITH UNIQUE STORE FRONTS AND OTHER YOUNG PEOPLE THEIR OWN AGE THE IMPORTANCE OF BUSINESS, ECONOMICS, ENTREPRENEURSHIP, ETHICS, CHARACTER, FINANCIAL LITERACY AND CAREER DEVELOPMENT. JUNIOR ACHIEVEMENT IS CURRENTLY CONDUCTING A FEASIBILITY STUDY TO DETERMINE EXACTLY HOW TO IMPLEMENT THESE LEARNING PROGRAMS IN WISCONSIN.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Intended Use of Endowment Funds:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: the organization's endowment funds are to be used for a variety of purposes including scholarship funds, capstone project, Wisconsin business hall of fame, and general operations.

Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Identifier: Procedure for Monitoring Grants in the U.S.:
Form990ScheduleIPartIV.Explanation: Schedule I, Part I, Line 2: the organization has a selection committee that reviews the applications and after awarding, but before payment, the students need to provide proof of enrollment in a college or university and maintain a minimum grade point average. Further, the organization issues the checks directly to the educational institution and never to the students.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 2

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The audit committee will review and approve the Form 990. A copy will then be sent to all board members for review.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: the board development committee reviews all the conflict of interest statements. Any issues that arise from the review will be brought to the Executive committee's attention.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: the president's salary is subject to board approval. Local and National compensation comparisons are reviewed. Key employees pay is reviewed against local and national data.
